<!-- FEATURED MEMBER STORY — Javier -->
<section class="featured-story" aria-labelledby="member-stories-heading">
  <div class="featured-story__inner">
    <div class="featured-story__card">
      <div class="featured-story__quote-mark" aria-hidden="true">"</div>
      <div class="featured-story__content">
        <blockquote class="featured-story__text">
          <p>I've absolutely loved my experience at The Gym of Tucson. When I first walked in, I honestly expected an intimidating environment full of super-buff guys throwing heavy weights around, yelling, and taking things way too seriously. Within my very first class, I realized how wrong I was.</p>
          <p>From day one, I was welcomed warmly and treated with genuine respect for my own pace, goals, and fitness journey. Every coach is knowledgeable, kind, and incredibly accommodating. Anytime I've had an injury, soreness, or limitation, they've always been able to modify exercises in a way that keeps me moving safely while still helping me get stronger.</p>
          <p>Since joining, I've lost around 20 pounds — but more importantly, I've done it in a healthy, sustainable way that actually feels maintainable long-term. This hasn't been about crash diets or temporary trends. It's been about building habits and strength that I know will stick.</p>
          <p>The community here is something special. They genuinely care about people and give back in meaningful ways. It feels like a second home — a place that's not only an investment in my health and future, but one that helps me show up better and stronger for my family and the people I love.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <footer class="featured-story__footer">
          <div class="featured-story__avatar" aria-hidden="true">J</div>
          <div class="featured-story__meta">
            <cite class="featured-story__name">Javier</cite>
            <span class="featured-story__detail">Member · Group Classes · Lost 20 lbs</span>
          </div>
        </footer>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

